# Plan: Add PulseBoard Channel Plugin

## Context

We are adding a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin to OpenClaw — a real-time bulletin board messaging platform. PulseBoard supports named "boards" (groups) and direct messages. This is a stub implementation following the established channel plugin patterns. Only new files are created under `extensions/pulseboard/`; no existing files are modified.

## Reference Patterns

Studied from existing plugins:
- **IRC** (`extensions/irc/`) — medium-complexity, multi-account, DMs + groups
- **Nostr** (`extensions/nostr/`) — simpler DM-only channel
- **Telegram** (`extensions/telegram/`) — full-featured reference

